&lt;p&gt;If you geek out over semantic layers and governance frameworks as much as you do over whiteboarding solutions with clients, you might be exactly who we&#39;re looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At InterWorks, Analytics Architects live at the intersection of technical depth and client partnership. You&#39;ll lead engagements from pre-sales through delivery, mentor consultants along the way, and help clients build analytics capabilities that actually stick after you&#39;re gone. It&#39;s a consulting role, which means variety is built in — and so is the opportunity to grow fast.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re not looking for someone who just executes. We need someone who can architect solutions, lead delivery teams with confidence, and earn client trust quickly. The ability to bridge what&#39;s technically optimal and what a client can realistically adopt is what sets the best candidates apart.&amp;nbsp; Not deep in Sigma yet? If your dbt, BI and data modeling foundations are strong, we still want to hear from you. Sigma can be learned. The craft underneath it is harder to find.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location Preferences: &amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;This role has a strong preference for candidates in Raleigh-Durham, NC. Remote candidates in Central or Eastern time zones will be considered.&amp;nbsp; Remote work may be possible depending on the situation, let’s chat.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary Range:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;$130,000–160,000, depending on experience and qualifications&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead enterprise analytics engagements end-to-end — from scoping and solution design through delivery, documentation, and client enablement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect and build governed metric definitions, reusable data models, and self-service analytics that scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver Sigma Apps, including input tables, write-back workflows, and workbook-as-product patterns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and implement AI-enabling data infrastructure: context pipelines, metadata layers, and governance frameworks that make data assets discoverable, trustworthy, and ready for AI consumption at scale.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Architect systems integrations that connect CDWs, semantic layers, BI surfaces, and operational systems into coherent, governed data products.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a trusted pre-sales partner — help scope engagements, contribute to proposals, and help prospects understand the art of the possible.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and evangelize software and analytics engineering standards — metric definitions, CI/CD, data model conventions, and governance patterns — across client organizations and internally at InterWorks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor consultants on project-based engagements, providing technical guidance and supporting professional development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build capability areas through internal solutions, reusable assets, and external partnerships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
